subtitleNullable: All 104 labels for the Flower Classification With TPUs Competition
descriptionNullable:
### Context

While the [Flower Classification With TPUs](https://www.kaggle.com/c/flower-classification-with-tpus) competitions has the image data arranged in a very convenient way, the dataset itself doesn't have their human-friendly names (e.g. `pink primrose`, `tiger lily`). You have to obtain the human-friendly names from the [Getting Started Notebook](https://www.kaggle.com/mgornergoogle/getting-started-with-100-flowers-on-tpu/) for the competition, where they are available as a list in a code cell.

### Content

This dataset is a ready-to-use CSV version of that list. It contains a single string column called `class`. There are exactly 104 rows, one for each label in the dataset for the competition, containing the human-friendly names of the label.


### Acknowledgements

Thank you to [Martin Görner](https://www.kaggle.com/mgornergoogle) for making the list in the first place.
